      "text": [
        " أَبُو عَبْدِ اَللَّهِ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ : «لاَ بَأْسَ بِأَنْ تَطُوفَ اَلْمَرْأَةُ غَيْرَ مَخْفُوضَةٍ فَأَمَّا اَلرَّجُلُ فَلاَ يَطُوفُ إِلاَّ مَخْتُوناً »."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.2814 - Hariz and Ibrahim ibn Umar narrated that Abu Abdullah (as) said:\n\"There is no harm if a woman performs tawaf without being circumcised. As for a man, he should not perform tawaf unless he is circumcised.\""
        ]
      }
    },
